# A7670C Arduino Library for ESP32

A clean, full-featured C++ Arduino library for the **SIM A7670C LTE module** connected to an **ESP32** over Hardware UART.

---

## Features

| Feature | AT Commands Used |
|---|---|
| Power on / off / reset via PWRKEY | GPIO pulse |
| Mobile data (PDP context) ON / OFF | `AT+CGDCONT`, `AT+CGACT` |
| HTTP GET / POST / PUT / DELETE | `AT+HTTPINIT`, `AT+HTTPACTION`, `AT+HTTPREAD` |
| MQTT connect / publish / subscribe | `AT+SMCONF`, `AT+SMCONN`, `AT+SMPUB`, `AT+SMSUB` |
| Send SMS | `AT+CMGS` |
| Receive SMS (callback on new message) | `+CMTI` URC |
| Read / list / delete SMS | `AT+CMGR`, `AT+CMGL`, `AT+CMGD` |
| Dial outgoing voice call | `ATD` |
| Answer / hang-up call | `ATA`, `ATH` |
| Incoming call detection (callback) | `RING`, `+CLIP` URC |
| Supply voltage (mV) | `AT+CBC` |
| Signal strength (CSQ / RSSI / BER) | `AT+CSQ` |
| Network registration status | `AT+CREG` |
| IMEI / ICCID / Operator / Firmware | `AT+CGSN`, `AT+CCID`, `AT+COPS`, `AT+CGMR` |
| Raw AT command access | `sendAT()` |

---

## Wiring

```
ESP32 GPIO16 (RX1)  ──────────►  A7670C TXD
ESP32 GPIO17 (TX1)  ◄──────────  A7670C RXD
ESP32 GPIO4         ──────────►  A7670C PWRKEY
GND                 ───────────  GND (common)
3.3 V / 4.2 V supply via dedicated LDO (do NOT power from ESP32 3V3 pin)
```

> **Note:** The A7670C draws up to 2 A peak during TX bursts. Use a dedicated supply capable of at least 2 A.

---

## Installation

1. Download or clone this repository.
2. Copy the `A7670C` folder into your Arduino `libraries/` directory.
3. Restart the Arduino IDE.
4. Open `File → Examples → A7670C → FullDemo`.

---

## Quick Start

```cpp
#include "A7670C.h"

// Serial1: RX=GPIO16, TX=GPIO17, PWRKEY=GPIO4
A7670C gsm(Serial1, 16, 17, 4);

void setup() {
    Serial.begin(115200);
    gsm.setDebug(Serial);
    gsm.setDebugEnabled(true);
    gsm.begin();
}

void loop() {
    gsm.loop();   // Required – processes all incoming URCs
}
```

---

## API Reference

### Lifecycle

```cpp
bool begin();               // Init UART, power on, wait ready
void end();                 // Graceful power off
void loop();                // Call every iteration of Arduino loop()
bool powerOn();             // Assert PWRKEY pulse
bool powerOff();            // AT+CPOWD=1
bool reset();               // PWRKEY reset pulse
bool isAlive();             // AT ping
bool waitReady(ms);         // Block until module responds
```

### Module Info

```cpp
String    getIMEI();
String    getICCID();
String    getOperator();
String    getFirmwareVersion();
RegStatus getNetworkStatus();  // NOT_REGISTERED, REGISTERED_HOME, ROAMING, etc.
```

### Signal & Voltage

```cpp
SignalInfo info = gsm.getSignalStrength();
// info.csq   – Raw CSQ (0–31, 99=unknown)
// info.rssi  – dBm (-113 to -51)
// info.ber   – Bit error rate

int mv = gsm.getVoltage_mV();   // e.g. 4150 = 4.15 V
```

### Internet ON / OFF

```cpp
gsm.enableInternet("airtelgprs.com");   // Pass your carrier APN
gsm.disableInternet();
bool up = gsm.isInternetEnabled();
```

### HTTP REST API

```cpp
// Simple GET
HttpResponse r = gsm.httpGet("http://api.example.com/data");
Serial.println(r.statusCode);   // 200
Serial.println(r.body);

// POST with JSON
HttpResponse r = gsm.httpPost(
    "https://api.example.com/event",
    "{\"temp\":23.5}",
    "application/json"
);

// Full control
HttpResponse resp;
gsm.httpRequest(HttpMethod::PUT, url, body, contentType, resp);
```

### MQTT

```cpp
// Configure once
gsm.mqttConfigure("myClientId", "broker.hivemq.com", 1883, "user", "pass");

// Connect
gsm.mqttConnect();

// Subscribe
gsm.mqttSubscribe("sensors/cmd", 0);

// Publish
gsm.mqttPublish("sensors/data", "{\"val\":42}", 0, false);

// Receive – register callback before connect
gsm.onMqttMessage([](const String& topic, const String& payload) {
    Serial.println(topic + " → " + payload);
});

// Disconnect
gsm.mqttDisconnect();
```

### SMS

```cpp
// Send
gsm.smsSend("+919876543210", "Hello from ESP32!");

// Read one
SmsMessage msg = gsm.smsRead(1);
Serial.println(msg.sender + ": " + msg.text);

// List all
SmsMessage msgs[10];
int n = gsm.smsList(msgs, 10, "ALL");

// Delete
gsm.smsDelete(1);        // delete index 1
gsm.smsDelete(1, 4);     // delete all

// Callback on new SMS
gsm.onSms([](SmsMessage msg) {
    Serial.println("New SMS from " + msg.sender);
});
```

### Voice Calls

```cpp
// Outgoing
gsm.callDial("+919876543210");
delay(8000);
gsm.callHangUp();

// Incoming – register callback
gsm.onRing([](const String& number) {
    Serial.println("Ring from " + number);
    gsm.callAnswer();
    delay(5000);
    gsm.callHangUp();
});

// Check active call
bool active = gsm.callIsActive();
```

### Raw AT Access

```cpp
String response = gsm.sendAT("AT+CPSI?", "OK", 5000);
if (gsm.lastOK()) {
    Serial.println(response);
}
```

---

## Configuration Macros (`A7670C.h`)

| Macro | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `A7670C_DEFAULT_BAUD` | 115200 | UART baud rate |
| `A7670C_CMD_TIMEOUT_MS` | 5000 | Default AT command timeout |
| `A7670C_HTTP_TIMEOUT_MS` | 30000 | HTTP request timeout |
| `A7670C_MQTT_TIMEOUT_MS` | 10000 | MQTT connect timeout |
| `A7670C_RX_BUFFER_SIZE` | 2048 | Internal RX buffer |
| `A7670C_MAX_PAYLOAD_LEN` | 512 | Max HTTP body read size |

